Overall, this was a very good stir fry. It was very, very flavorful and fairly easy to make. I basically followed the recipe with just a few changes. I doubled the amount of both sauces as most people recommended (both the marinade for the meat as well as the amount of soy sauce w/ sugar). I used pork tenderloin and added water chestnuts and baby corn (one can of each). I'm not a huge ginger fan so I only used it when I cooked the veggies (about 1 teaspoon total). I used a bit more garlic than the recipe calls for. I also added a couple of minutes to the cooking times (I added a couple of minutes when cooking the veggies and again when I cooked the meat).

