Rating: 2
I am only giving this recipe 2 stars because the preparation instructions need major improvement. The meat should be very quickly stir-fried (and removed) before the veggies instead of doing the veggies first and having to reheat them, thereby making them soggy and overcooked. I added a single, large crown of broccoli (broken into florets and nuked for a few minutes in a little water) because there were just not enough vegetables. I also used a fresh chile pepper instead of flakes, Shaoxing wine instead of the sherry (vastly better), roasted sesame oil (Kadoya brand is excellent). To make adequate sauce, I added a cup of chicken broth w/ a bit more cornstarch. I also recommend brown instead of plain sugar. With these improvements, the entrée is much better. I served mine over long-grain brown rice. I'd make it again but only with the same revisions.

